    <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
mattmcbear wrote:&lt;BR&gt;Of course the obvious answer instead of devolving items, (which is a bad idea from the start, if I wanted to play that system I would have been playing WOW and besides who wants to drop 20k on a piece of armor that will eventually decay) is to have npc merchants that will give tradeskillers a small profit for want they make. Then the npc merchant can sell the thing higher or distroy the item. This would allow the tradeskiller to recoop some money, make a profit and if someone wants to buy an item their prices would be lower then the npc merchant(assuming the tradeskill item that the npc merchant isn't distoyed) allowing for repeat business. Now the npc merchants can be coded so that you have to be tagged to sell to them it could be tied to someones tradeskill level. For instance if you try and sell that piece banded armor you have to have the skill of say 100 to sell it to the special merchantso not every one could just sell to them.&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Unfortunately, the reality is that there are bots that will make someone millions of plat if we allow any sort of sell back for profit.&amp;nbsp; The only&amp;nbsp;way I see is&amp;nbsp;to only allow a limited number of sells... and at that point, it might as well just be a quest, that is only repeatable once a day/week or some such.&amp;nbsp; Limited sells outside that would be a code change.&amp;nbsp; At this time I have no plans to implement such "tradeskill for profit" quests.</description>
