    <item>
      <title>De-evolving tradeskill recipes.  Please read, are you in favor?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=12527#M12527</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;Would you favor for the creation of recipes to make de-evolving items that upon their final stage of evolution went to &lt;b&gt;no rent&lt;/b&gt; status?&lt;br&gt;1) They could have several levels of de-evolution, the first few stages they could be VERY good items.&lt;br&gt;2) Eventually they would lose their useful status, however they could be resold (not made no drop) and useful in another recipe (with the risk of failure to destroy it) to bring their stats back to full power and prolong their use.&lt;br&gt;3) By making tradeskill items that eventually poof or useful to be made whole again, you can get a repeat customer (like the potion vendors).&lt;br&gt;-----&lt;br&gt;Example of an item with 10 Stages of Evolution (De-evolution)&lt;br&gt;As an item is used it gains experience and evolves into a lower state.&lt;br&gt;1st stage is the base.  Item is at it's peak.&lt;br&gt;2nd stage the item has lost some of its lustur. Failure risk of combining to bring it to 1st stage low (low trivial recipe).&lt;br&gt;.&lt;br&gt;.&lt;br&gt;.&lt;br&gt;9th stage the item has lost most of its lustur.  Failure risk of combining to bring it to 1st stage is high (high trivial recipe).&lt;br&gt;10th stage the item has still lost most of its lustur.  The item is now no rent.  Failure risk of combining it to 1st stage is the original difficulty (very high trivial).&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
