      <title>Re: De-evolving tradeskill recipes.  Please read, are you in favor?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=12715#M12715</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;This just sounds like another thing that would take me away from actually having fun.  I would hate this.  I am thinking of RL things that &amp;quot;decay&amp;quot; and to my mind most things I acquire take years to go bad and cause trouble.  Granted I don't wear armor but I like fantasy to stay fantasy.  Why make things like real life?  Why make it so complicated that people get upset and don't want to play.  I was horrified when friends playing other games told me about this.  I wouldn't want to waste my limited game play time by having to repair a much needed item.  I am sure there are other casual gamers who already don't have time for farming and camping for plat and items and so do not amass copious amounts of plat, and this would just be another way to separate those players from those who have excess amount of time to play.</description>
