      <title>Re: De-evolving tradeskill recipes.  Please read, are you in favor?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=12716#M12716</link>
      <description>I agree with it, but I would like the combines for the items to involve several high level subcombines within the skill (relative to the item) with more common drops/forages. I could never see this working with say Metallic Scales or Drake Bones or Blue Iridescent Troll Teeth as the cost would be out of proportion with the item returned. Now if you spent 2-3K to make an item similar to what you might get from a Monster Mission and it lasted a couple of weeks, that seems fair.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If this kind of tradeskilling were in parallel with items that don't de evolve, it will keep the folks who hate upkeep happy (until they see how nice de evolving items can be or how cheap).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;As far as EQ is concerned why not make arrows that are immune to the effect of Endless Quiver? You still have it for most arrows out there, but newer more powerful arrows would be used up.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;What I really would like is a tradeskill path that uses a tougher standard than RNG to create items of worth, thereby making it easier for EQ to allow worthwhile items.&lt;br&gt;Multiple high level subcombines or some form of skill test(300 range?) means greater numbers of failures, but it the items are not too expensive, it would still be worth it.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Flatley Riverdancer</description>
