      <title>Re: De-evolving tradeskill recipes.  Please read, are you in favor?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=12733#M12733</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV align=left&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P align=left&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV align=left&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Dev-Ngreth wrote:&lt;BR&gt;I SOOOO wanted the AAAA to explode for say 3k damage... (not enough to be more than an inconvenience for most of the intended audience).&amp;nbsp; But the current game system just did not allow for it.&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P align=left&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Let me first say, that in no way shape or form do I consider myself a tradeskiller, nor do I ever plan on being one.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P align=left&gt;Your comment both excited me and filled me with dread.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P align=left&gt;I really don't think a damage to player factor ever needs to be considered for tradeskilling, least-wise I would never consider that "fun". *Maybe* if it never exceeded the threshold similar to the bristlebane pet thingies poison food/drink.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P align=left&gt;However, your comment sparked an idea that I can only hope to be considered:&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P align=left&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Visual Particle Effects on tradeskill combines.&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P align=left&gt;Consider the fireworks clickies, or the Priest of Discord port to Dranik's Scar particles... very cool effects.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P align=left&gt;I think it would add quite a bit of "fun factor" to tradeskilling if various skills and items had a wide range of particle effects when you combine (success/fails).&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P align=left&gt;Of course, this does imply that *someone* has to take the time to make new particle&amp;nbsp;effects and then attach the right skills/items/combine to the right particles.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P align=left&gt;Extra work? Yes. Worth it? I think so (from a non-tradeskiller).&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P align=left&gt;Obviously this would require code support as well, and no doubt it should have some type of configuration on the display particles options so that people who do not like them or it lags too much can turm them down/off.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
