      <title>Re: De-evolving tradeskill recipes.  Please read, are you in favor?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=12641#M12641</link>
      <description>I've let several days pass by before rechecking this thread.  My own intention was not to implement this system for current items; however, to suggest it for future expansions/recipes/items.  I've read many posts from devs concerning SoE's outlook on more powerful items, basicly they do not want to put them in.  They want to see the game maintain its healthy growth without becoming too &amp;quot;top heavy&amp;quot; (everyone running around as gods).  Their focus has been to not create items TOO good, despite the players desire to have the BEST of the BEST for their character.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;In other words, I think this type of system should be implemented for new items that exhibit the characteristic of the - Best of the Best &amp;amp; VERY High End Tradeskill Level Gear.  This could add to the value of tradeskill type epics and select end game items from each expansion.  With no level requirements, the items exist at their prime values; however, the rate they decay is higher at the lower levels and will decay closer to their useful status.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;(Oh and 10 levels was just an example, you could easily only have lower evolution levels)&lt;br&gt;EXAMPLE ONLY: For staggered decay rate based upon experience earned at the level breakdowns.&lt;br&gt;10:    70 Good for 20 AA's worth of exp. 50 Good for 5 AA's worth of exp.   25 Good for 5 Levels' worth of exp.&lt;br&gt;9:      70 Good for 40 AA's worth of exp. 50 Good for 10 AA's worth of exp. 25 Good for 6 Levels' worth of exp.&lt;br&gt;8:      70 Good for 60 AA's worth of exp. 50 Good for 15 AA's worth of exp. 25 Good for 4 Levels' worth of exp.&lt;br&gt;7:      70 Good for 30 AA's worth of exp. 50 Good for 25 AA's worth of exp. 25 Good for 3 Levels' worth of exp.&lt;br&gt;6:      70 Good for 15 AA's worth of exp. 50 Good for 20 AA's worth of exp. 25 Good for 2 Levels' worth of exp.&lt;br&gt;5:      70 Good for 7 AA's worth of exp.   50 Good for 10 AA's worth of exp. 25 Good for 6 Levels' worth of exp.&lt;br&gt;4:      70 Good for 3 AA's worth of exp.   50 Good for 8 AA's worth of exp.   25 Good for 15 Levels' worth of exp.&lt;br&gt;3:      70 Good for 2 AA's worth of exp.   50 Good for 3 AA's worth of exp.   25 Good for 25 Level's worth of exp.&lt;br&gt;2:      70 Good for 1 AA's worth of exp.   50 Good for 1 AA's worth of exp.   25 Good for 20 Level's worth of exp.&lt;br&gt;1:      70 (No Rent) 10pp&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I am also in disagreement about the price to combine the old items to that of their refurbished appearance.  The idea was not meant to be a platsink, but an alternative tradeskill interaction between players.  To bring an item back to it's old level should be within the 100pp to 900pp range and maintain the risk of it being destroyed where the risk is lower if it is constantly being maintained.  For those wishing new 'clickies' the best levels could easily have an effect that decays in value with the item.  I also realize that with many item slots and augments in existence that it &amp;quot;could&amp;quot; get expensive to maintain gear; however, old content with permanent items will help with these costs (especially if you have to remove an augment before giving it to a tradeskiller).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Alternative recipes could still exist so journeyman tradeskillers could also try their hand at making the lower level versions.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;(Thoughts on failure rates, etc.)&lt;br&gt;Level 1 item &amp;amp; 900plat vendor item can bring it back to level 10: Highest risk of combine failure.&lt;br&gt;Level 1 item &amp;amp; 800plat vendor item can bring it back to level 9:   .&lt;br&gt;Level 1 item &amp;amp; 700plat vendor item can bring it back to level 8    .&lt;br&gt;.&lt;br&gt;.&lt;br&gt;.&lt;br&gt;Level 1 item &amp;amp; 100plat vendor item can bring it back to level 2: Lowest risk of combine failure.&lt;br&gt;.&lt;br&gt;Level 2 - Level 10&lt;br&gt;Level 3 - Level 10&lt;br&gt;Level 4 - Level 10&lt;br&gt;.&lt;br&gt;Level 8 item &amp;amp; 200plat vendor item can bring it back to level 10: Moderate risk of combine failure.&lt;br&gt;Level 8 item &amp;amp; 100plat vendor item can bring it back to level 9: Low risk of combine failure.&lt;br&gt;Level 9 item &amp;amp; 100plat vendor item can bring it back to level 10: Low risk of combine failure.&lt;br&gt;-----&lt;br&gt;I personally feel that if implemented properly, de-evolution can permit very nice items that everyone can use and grow people's interest in learning tradeskills.&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
